Amplitude is a comprehensive product analytics and experimentation platform that enables organizations to understand user behavior, optimize product experiences, and drive growth through data-driven insights. The platform centers around event-based analytics with integrated experimentation capabilities, session replay, and customer data platform (CDP) functionality.

## Core Product Architecture

**Amplitude Analytics** serves as the foundational product, providing real-time user behavior tracking through an event-based architecture. The platform captures user interactions as events with associated properties, enabling detailed analysis of user journeys, feature adoption, and retention patterns. The analytics core includes customizable dashboards, automated event tracking through Autocapture, and a comprehensive charting system with specialized visualizations.

**Amplitude Experiment** provides feature flagging and A/B testing capabilities with advanced statistical analysis, including sequential testing, CUPED variance reduction, and multi-armed bandit optimization. The experimentation platform integrates directly with analytics for unified user identification and exposure tracking.

**Amplitude Session Replay** captures user interactions for qualitative analysis, with configurable sampling rates and privacy controls. Session recordings integrate with analytics events for contextual debugging and user experience optimization.

**Customer Data Platform (CDP)** functionality includes audience segmentation, data governance, and integration management through source and destination catalogs supporting hundreds of third-party platforms.

